                <h1>How Anne Frank Met Her Tragic End</h1>
                <p>Anne Frank died in the Bergen-Belsen concentration camp in March 1945, shortly before the camp was liberated. She succumbed to typhus, which ravaged the camp due to overcrowding and poor hygiene. Her death came just weeks after her sister Margot died, marking a tragic end to the young girl's life, full of hope despite the horrors of war.</p>
